[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: GHOST SuperPrompt Projection and Prompt Builder Requirements
UID: GHOST-SUPERPROMPT-PROJECTION
VERSION: 0.1
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text
  AUTO_LEVELS: On
  NODE_IN_TOC: True

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 1. Purpose, Scope, and Current Implementation Map

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This document defines the detailed current requirements for SuperPrompt projection, prompt-ready rendering, and the live Prompt Builder workflow through A4.

Current implementation truth is derived from the provided source files, primarily:

- ragstream/orchestration/super_prompt.py;
- ragstream/orchestration/superprompt_projector.py;
- ragstream/app/pipeline_runner.py;
- ragstream/app/controller.py;
- ragstream/app/ui_actions.py;
- ragstream/app/ui_streamlit.py;
- ragstream/retrieval/retriever_mem.py; and
- the A2, A3, and A4 stage implementations that write into SuperPrompt.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: SuperPrompt Projection and Prompt Builder Scope
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall provide a projection and Prompt Builder capability that converts the current SuperPrompt state into retrieval-oriented projections, A3 comparison text, stage-visible engineered prompt previews, and the current final prompt_ready representation.

This file shall define current implemented behavior through A4 and shall explicitly separate that behavior from the unfinished external LLM-call/send boundary, postponed A5 behavior, and future global Hard Rule integration.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-CONTEXT-INTEGRATION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-SOURCE-AUTHORITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Source-Code Authority
STATEMENT: >>>
The detailed behavior in this file shall follow the provided current Python source code and active runtime configuration.

Legacy Prompt Builder descriptions shall be treated as intent only where they are not wired into the current runtime.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-LEGACY-STUB
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Legacy PromptBuilder Stub Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
A legacy prompt_builder.py stub whose build method returns a placeholder value shall not be represented as the current operational prompt-assembly implementation.

The current executable assembly path shall remain SuperPrompt.compose_prompt_ready() delegating to SuperPromptProjector.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 2. SuperPrompt Projection State Contract

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPrompt remains the authoritative run-local state object. SuperPromptProjector derives text representations from that state and writes the rendered strings back into the same object.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-AUTHORITATIVE-STATE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Authoritative Shared State
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPrompt shall remain the authoritative shared runtime state for the active prompt-building run.

SuperPromptProjector shall derive projections from SuperPrompt and shall not become a parallel owner of independent prompt truth.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-LIFECYCLE-FIELDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Lifecycle Projection Inputs
STATEMENT: >>>
The current SuperPrompt projection state shall include stage, model_target, and history_of_stages.

The recognized current stage values are raw, preprocessed, a2, retrieval, reranked, a3, a4, and the reserved a5 value.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-AUTHORITATIVE-STATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-BODY-FIELDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Canonical Prompt Body Fields
STATEMENT: >>>
The current SuperPrompt body shall support these canonical fields:

- system;
- task;
- audience;
- role;
- tone;
- depth;
- confidence;
- evidence_policy;
- context;
- purpose;
- format; and
- text.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-AUTHORITATIVE-STATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-BODY-DEFAULTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Body Defaults
STATEMENT: >>>
A newly constructed SuperPrompt shall currently initialize system to consultant, tone to neutral, depth to high, and evidence_policy to normal, while the other optional canonical fields begin empty.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-BODY-FIELDS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-EXTRAS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Runtime Extras
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPrompt.extras shall remain the free-form run-local location for diagnostics and namespaced stage metadata required by current projection behavior.

Extras shall not be described as a durable store or as a general Blackboard protocol.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-AUTHORITATIVE-STATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-QUERY-FIELD
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Effective Retrieval Query Field
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPrompt.effective_retrieval_query_text shall hold the current effective retrieval query prepared by preprocessing/projection policy for document and memory retrieval.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-AUTHORITATIVE-STATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ACTIVEBRIEF-FIELDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: ActiveBrief Runtime Fields
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPrompt shall provide active_memory_brief_title and active_memory_brief fields for the latest memory-retrieval ActiveBrief snapshot.

Current previous-conversation rendering shall still follow the relation-classifier snapshot stored in extras as defined by the current projector implementation.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-AUTHORITATIVE-STATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-MEMORY-FIELDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Runtime Fields
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPrompt shall provide memory_context_text for synthesized query-relevant Memory Context and memory_context_pack for the run-local raw memory retrieval artifact.

The raw pack shall not be treated as durable memory truth.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-AUTHORITATIVE-STATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-DOCUMENT-FIELDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Document Runtime Fields
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPrompt shall provide base_context_chunks, views_by_stage, final_selection_ids, and S_CTX_MD for document retrieval, stage ordering/status, selected identifiers, and condensed document context.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-AUTHORITATIVE-STATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RENDERED-FIELDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Rendered Prompt Fields
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPrompt shall provide System_MD, Prompt_MD, S_CTX_MD, Attachments_MD, and prompt_ready as current rendered or renderable prompt artifacts.

SuperPromptProjector shall update System_MD, Prompt_MD, and prompt_ready during composition.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-AUTHORITATIVE-STATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RECENT-CONVERSATION-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: recentConversation Current Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
The current SuperPrompt contains a recentConversation field, but the provided current SuperPromptProjector does not render that field into prompt_ready.

Requirements shall not claim current recentConversation rendering without additional implementation evidence.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-AUTHORITATIVE-STATE

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3. Projection Entry Points and Ownership

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-WRAPPER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Stable Composition Wrapper
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPrompt.compose_prompt_ready() shall remain the stable public wrapper for central prompt-ready rendering and shall delegate to SuperPromptProjector for the current implementation.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-PROJECTOR-CONSTRUCTOR
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Projector Input Validation
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPromptProjector construction shall reject a missing SuperPrompt reference rather than creating an unbound projector.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-DERIVED-LOGIC
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Derived Projection Logic Ownership
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPromptProjector shall own derived text projections from current SuperPrompt state, including retrieval query text, A3 comparison prompt text, system/configuration Markdown, current-request Markdown, supporting-context Markdown, and prompt_ready assembly.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-NO-STAGE-ALGORITHM-OWNERSHIP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Upstream Algorithm Ownership
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPromptProjector shall not own A2 selection, document retrieval, reranking, A3 usefulness classification, A4 condensation, memory candidate scoring, memory compression, or Memory Context synthesis.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 4. Retrieval Query Projection

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The projector currently derives retrieval query text from TASK, PURPOSE, CONTEXT, prompt materiality, topic relation, and the ActiveBrief snapshot prepared by the prompt-relation classifier.

30_preprocessing_prompt_functions.sdoc owns the routing semantics. This section records the current projection implementation used by downstream retrieval.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-QUERY-INPUTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Query Projection Inputs
STATEMENT: >>>
Retrieval query projection shall read task, purpose, and context from SuperPrompt.body and shall read activebrief_prompt_materiality, activebrief_topic_relation, and activebrief_relation_activebrief from SuperPrompt.extras.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-QUERY-STRONG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Strong Prompt Query Projection
STATEMENT: >>>
For STRONG prompts with SAME_TOPIC, RELATED_DOMAIN, or IRRELEVANT topic relation, the current retrieval query projection shall use current TASK, PURPOSE, and CONTEXT without adding ActiveBrief content.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-QUERY-INPUTS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-QUERY-WEAK-SAME
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Weak Same-Topic Query Projection
STATEMENT: >>>
For a WEAK SAME_TOPIC prompt, the current retrieval query projection shall add the full ActiveBrief body as a previous memory summary after the current TASK, PURPOSE, and CONTEXT blocks.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-QUERY-INPUTS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-QUERY-WEAK-RELATED
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Weak Related-Domain Query Projection
STATEMENT: >>>
For a WEAK RELATED_DOMAIN prompt, the current retrieval query projection shall add only the ActiveBrief title after the current TASK, PURPOSE, and CONTEXT blocks.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-QUERY-INPUTS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-QUERY-WEAK-IRRELEVANT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Weak Irrelevant Query Suppression
STATEMENT: >>>
For a WEAK IRRELEVANT prompt, the current retrieval query projection shall return an empty query so document retrieval can be suppressed by the upstream routing contract.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-QUERY-INPUTS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-QUERY-BLOCK-ORDER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Query Block Order
STATEMENT: >>>
When present, retrieval query blocks shall be emitted in this order:

1. TASK;
2. PURPOSE;
3. CONTEXT; and
4. permitted previous-memory title or summary.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-QUERY-INPUTS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-QUERY-EMPTY-ERROR
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Unexpected Empty Query Error
STATEMENT: >>>
Outside the explicit WEAK IRRELEVANT suppression route, query projection shall raise an error when TASK, PURPOSE, and CONTEXT produce no query text.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-QUERY-INPUTS

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 5. A3 Comparison Prompt Projection

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The current projector also prepares the request-under-evaluation used by A3. The evidence-selection semantics remain owned by 43_evidence_selection_and_condensation.sdoc.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-A3-WRAPPER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Evaluation Wrapper
STATEMENT: >>>
The A3 comparison projection shall wrap the current request and any permitted ActiveBrief continuity material inside one user_prompt_under_evaluation structure.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-A3-FULL-BRIEF
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Full ActiveBrief Routes
STATEMENT: >>>
The current A3 comparison projection shall include the full ActiveBrief body for:

- STRONG SAME_TOPIC;
- STRONG RELATED_DOMAIN;
- WEAK SAME_TOPIC; and
- WEAK IRRELEVANT.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-A3-WRAPPER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-A3-TITLE-ONLY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 ActiveBrief Title-Only Routes
STATEMENT: >>>
The current A3 comparison projection shall include only the ActiveBrief title for:

- STRONG IRRELEVANT; and
- WEAK RELATED_DOMAIN.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-A3-WRAPPER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-A3-NO-CONTEXT-FABRICATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3 Missing ActiveBrief Handling
STATEMENT: >>>
When the selected A3 projection route permits ActiveBrief content but the corresponding title or body is empty, the projector shall omit that block rather than fabricate continuity text.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-A3-WRAPPER

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 6. System and Configuration Rendering

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-SYSTEM-HEADING
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: System Section
STATEMENT: >>>
System rendering shall emit a top-level System section and shall place the current body.system value directly below it when present.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-CONFIG-SECTION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Configuration Section
STATEMENT: >>>
System rendering shall emit a Configuration section after the System section.

When corresponding values are present, configuration lines shall be emitted in this order:

1. Role;
2. Audience;
3. Tone;
4. Depth;
5. Confidence; and
6. Evidence Policy identifier when the policy produces a rendered policy block.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-EVIDENCE-POLICY-PRECEDENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Evidence Policy Identifier Precedence
STATEMENT: >>>
The current renderer shall resolve the evidence-policy identifier in this order:

1. extras.a2_selected_ids.evidence_policy;
2. body.evidence_policy; and
3. normal as fallback.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-CONFIG-SECTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-EVIDENCE-POLICY-NORMAL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Normal Evidence Policy Rendering
STATEMENT: >>>
When the resolved evidence-policy identifier is empty or normal, the current renderer shall not add a separate Evidence Policy instruction block.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-EVIDENCE-POLICY-PRECEDENCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-EVIDENCE-POLICY-LOCAL-CONTEXT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current local_context_first Policy Rendering
STATEMENT: >>>
When the current code identifier local_context_first is selected, the renderer shall add the configured local/project/history-first evidence instructions defined in SuperPromptProjector.

This identifier describes one current policy option and shall not be used to redefine GHOST as a local-first product.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-EVIDENCE-POLICY-PRECEDENCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-EVIDENCE-POLICY-STRICT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: strict_history_and_online_fact_check Rendering
STATEMENT: >>>
When strict_history_and_online_fact_check is selected, the renderer shall add the current configured instructions to prioritize available prompt/history/memory/project evidence, verify external unstable facts online when possible, cite evidence when possible, and identify missing evidence instead of inventing it.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-EVIDENCE-POLICY-PRECEDENCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-EVIDENCE-POLICY-UNKNOWN
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Unknown Evidence Policy Rendering
STATEMENT: >>>
A resolved evidence-policy identifier not explicitly recognized by the current projector shall not create an invented policy instruction block.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-EVIDENCE-POLICY-PRECEDENCE

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 7. Current User Request Rendering

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-REQUEST-SECTION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current User Request Section
STATEMENT: >>>
Prompt rendering shall emit a top-level Current User Request section after System and Configuration.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-REQUEST-PRIORITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Request Priority Instruction
STATEMENT: >>>
The Current User Request section shall state that the current request has highest priority and that later memory and retrieved context are supporting background only.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-REQUEST-SECTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-REQUEST-TASK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Task Block
STATEMENT: >>>
The renderer shall emit a Task subsection and shall write the current body.task value into it.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-REQUEST-SECTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-REQUEST-OPTIONALS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Optional Request Blocks
STATEMENT: >>>
After Task, the renderer shall emit non-empty optional request subsections in this order:

1. Purpose;
2. Context;
3. Format; and
4. Text.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-REQUEST-SECTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-REQUEST-NO-A2-IN-TASK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Configuration Separation from Task
STATEMENT: >>>
A2-selected role, audience, tone, depth, confidence, and evidence policy shall remain in System/Configuration rendering and shall not be merged into the Task text as if they were part of the user's request.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-REQUEST-SECTION

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 8. Supporting Context Rendering

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Supporting context is rendered only when at least one permitted previous-summary/topic block, synthesized Memory Context, document summary, or stage-visible raw document evidence is available.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-SUPPORT-SECTION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Supporting Context Section
STATEMENT: >>>
When supporting content exists, the renderer shall emit a top-level Supporting Context section after the Current User Request and shall mark that material as supporting only.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-SUPPORT-EMPTY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Empty Supporting Context Omission
STATEMENT: >>>
When no previous-summary/topic block, Memory Context, document summary, or raw document evidence is available, the renderer shall omit the entire Supporting Context section.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-SUPPORT-SECTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ACTIVEBRIEF-SOURCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Previous-Conversation Projection Source
STATEMENT: >>>
The current previous-conversation summary/topic projection shall read the relation-classifier ActiveBrief snapshot from extras.activebrief_relation_activebrief together with activebrief_prompt_materiality and activebrief_topic_relation.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-SUPPORT-SECTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ACTIVEBRIEF-FULL-ROUTES
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Full Previous-Conversation Summary Routes
STATEMENT: >>>
The current renderer shall permit a full Previous Conversation Summary for:

- STRONG SAME_TOPIC;
- STRONG RELATED_DOMAIN;
- WEAK SAME_TOPIC; and
- WEAK IRRELEVANT.

When available, the summary may contain the ActiveBrief title and body.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ACTIVEBRIEF-SOURCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ACTIVEBRIEF-TITLE-ROUTES
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Previous-Conversation Topic-Only Routes
STATEMENT: >>>
The current renderer shall permit only the Previous Conversation Topic title for:

- STRONG IRRELEVANT; and
- WEAK RELATED_DOMAIN.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ACTIVEBRIEF-SOURCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-MEMORY-CONTEXT-SOURCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Context Source Precedence
STATEMENT: >>>
The renderer shall read synthesized Memory Context first from SuperPrompt.memory_context_text and, when that field is empty, shall fall back to extras.memory_context_text.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-SUPPORT-SECTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-MEMORY-CONTEXT-LABEL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Context Label and Priority
STATEMENT: >>>
Non-empty synthesized Memory Context shall be rendered under a Memory Context subsection and shall be identified as background support rather than as the current task.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-MEMORY-CONTEXT-SOURCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RAW-MEMORY-HIDDEN
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Raw Memory Retrieval Hidden by Default
STATEMENT: >>>
The normal current prompt-ready rendering path shall not display raw MemoryContextPack episodes, semantic chunks, or memory debug Markdown.

Raw memory debug Markdown may remain available for diagnostics through the backward-compatible debug renderer.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-MEMORY-CONTEXT-SOURCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-DOCUMENT-SUMMARY-SOURCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Document Summary Source
STATEMENT: >>>
The renderer shall read the condensed document evidence summary directly from SuperPrompt.S_CTX_MD.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-SUPPORT-SECTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-DOCUMENT-SUMMARY-LABEL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Retrieved Project Evidence Summary
STATEMENT: >>>
Non-empty S_CTX_MD shall be rendered under Retrieved Project Evidence Summary and shall be identified as supporting project evidence rather than as the current task.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-DOCUMENT-SUMMARY-SOURCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RAW-DOCUMENT-STAGES
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Raw Document Evidence Stage Visibility
STATEMENT: >>>
The current renderer may show raw retrieved document evidence before A4.

When SuperPrompt.stage is a4 or a5, the renderer shall hide raw document chunks from the normal prompt-ready preview.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-SUPPORT-SECTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RAW-DOCUMENT-STRUCTURE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Raw Document Evidence Structure
STATEMENT: >>>
Raw document evidence shall be rendered as a retrieved_chunks structure with per-chunk index, stable chunk identifier, optional source, optional score/status information, and sanitized chunk text.

Detailed A3/A4 sanitization and evidence semantics remain owned by 43_evidence_selection_and_condensation.sdoc.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RAW-DOCUMENT-STAGES

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-DOCUMENT-ORDERING
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Raw Document Ordering
STATEMENT: >>>
The current projector shall order raw document evidence by this precedence:

1. A3 stage rows when stage is a3;
2. final_selection_ids when present;
3. the current stage view when present; and
4. base_context_chunks order otherwise.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RAW-DOCUMENT-STAGES

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-DOCUMENT-ID-MAP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Temporary Chunk-ID Map
STATEMENT: >>>
Before ordered raw-document rendering, the current projector shall create a temporary map from stable chunk identifier to hydrated chunk object.

This behavior shall not be represented as semantic duplicate detection across different chunk identifiers or across Knowledge and Memory Context.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RAW-DOCUMENT-STAGES

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 9. Final prompt_ready Composition

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-COMPOSE-SYSTEM
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: System_MD Rebuild
STATEMENT: >>>
Each central composition call shall rebuild SuperPrompt.System_MD from current SuperPrompt state.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-COMPOSE-PROMPT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Prompt_MD Rebuild
STATEMENT: >>>
Each central composition call shall rebuild SuperPrompt.Prompt_MD from current SuperPrompt state.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-COMPOSE-ORDER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: prompt_ready Assembly Order
STATEMENT: >>>
The current central composer shall append non-empty prompt parts in this order:

1. System_MD;
2. Prompt_MD;
3. rendered Supporting Context; and
4. Attachments_MD.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-COMPOSE-JOIN
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Prompt Part Separation
STATEMENT: >>>
The current composer shall join non-empty prompt parts with blank-line separation, trim the result, assign it to SuperPrompt.prompt_ready, and return that same string.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-COMPOSE-ORDER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ATTACHMENTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Attachment Block Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
When SuperPrompt.Attachments_MD is already non-empty, the current composer shall append it after Supporting Context.

The provided current projection code does not itself load, parse, validate, or create attachment content.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-COMPOSE-ORDER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-NO-FINAL-ANSWER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Composition Is Not Answer Generation
STATEMENT: >>>
Assigning prompt_ready shall create an engineered prompt artifact and shall not generate a final answer to the user.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-COMPOSE-ORDER

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 10. Current Prompt Builder Runner

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The current Prompt Builder frontend runner executes one stage per Streamlit rerun cycle and writes intermediate snapshots into session state.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-STEPS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Executable Runner Steps
STATEMENT: >>>
The current live Prompt Builder runner shall execute these six steps in order:

1. Pre-Processing;
2. A2-PromptShaper;
3. Retrieval;
4. ReRanker or retrieval pass-through;
5. A3 NLI Gate; and
6. A4 Condenser.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-PROMPT-GUARD
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Prompt Input Guard
STATEMENT: >>>
The current runner shall reject empty or whitespace-only prompt input before pipeline execution.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-STEPS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-PROJECT-GUARD
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Active Project Guard
STATEMENT: >>>
The current runner shall reject execution when no active project is available.

The provided current runner therefore shall not be described as implementing a complete prompt-only mode that bypasses the project requirement.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-STEPS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-NEW-STATE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: New SuperPrompt at Preprocessing Start
STATEMENT: >>>
At the first automated runner step, the current implementation shall create a new SuperPrompt and pass it through controller preprocessing.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-STEPS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-MEMORY-RETRIEVAL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Retrieval in Retrieval Step
STATEMENT: >>>
During the current Retrieval runner step, the controller shall run document retrieval and shall also attempt Memory Retrieval when MemoryRetriever has been configured.

Memory output shall remain separately represented in SuperPrompt from document candidate views.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-STEPS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-RERANK-PASSTHROUGH
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: ReRanker Pass-Through
STATEMENT: >>>
When ColBERT reranking is disabled, the current runner shall skip the real reranker and shall rely on the retrieval-created A3-ready reranked pass-through view.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-STEPS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-SNAPSHOTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Stage Snapshots
STATEMENT: >>>
The current runner shall create deep-copy snapshots at the implemented inspection points sp_pre, sp_a2, sp_rtv, sp_rrk, sp_a3, and sp_a4.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-STEPS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-GUI-WRITEBACK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: GUI Prompt Preview Write-Back
STATEMENT: >>>
After each completed runner step, the current UI action shall store the updated SuperPrompt and shall write sp.prompt_ready into the GUI session-state engineered-prompt text field.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-STEPS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-STAGE-COMPOSITION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Stage Composition Calls
STATEMENT: >>>
Current stage implementations or runner actions shall recompose prompt_ready after preprocessing, A2, Retrieval, ReRanker/pass-through, A3, and A4 according to their current wiring.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-STEPS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-RUNNER-HARD-RULE-VISUAL
