[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 13. Acceptance Criteria

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-AC-ORDER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Composition Order
STATEMENT: >>>
Given a SuperPrompt containing non-empty system/configuration, current request, Memory Context, S_CTX_MD, and Attachments_MD, compose_prompt_ready shall place them in the order System/Configuration, Current User Request, Supporting Context, and Attachments.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-AC-A4-RAW-HIDDEN
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Raw Document Evidence Hidden After A4
STATEMENT: >>>
Given stage a4 and non-empty S_CTX_MD, normal prompt_ready rendering shall show Retrieved Project Evidence Summary and shall not show raw retrieved document chunks.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-AC-RAW-MEMORY-HIDDEN
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Raw Memory Hidden
STATEMENT: >>>
Given a populated MemoryContextPack and non-empty synthesized Memory Context, normal prompt_ready rendering shall show the synthesized Memory Context and shall not show raw memory candidates by default.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-AC-RUNNER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Runner Through A4
STATEMENT: >>>
Given valid prompt input, an active project, configured controller components, and no stage failure, the current Prompt Builder runner shall complete the six executable steps through A4, preserve stage snapshots, and leave the latest engineered prompt in SuperPrompt.prompt_ready and GUI session state.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SP-PROJECTION-AC-CURRENT-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: No False Completion Claim
STATEMENT: >>>
Inspection of the provided current code shall not identify a live global Hard Rule engine, completed A5 stage, dedicated operational PromptBuilder class, or completed external LLM-call/send action after prompt_ready composition.
<<<
RELATIONS:
